The paper discusses multi-task learning, which is a common topic in machine learning. The paper also introduces a new formulation for multi-task learning, which is likely to be of interest to researchers in the field. Based on this, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses applications in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL), which are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses theoretical results related to learning to learn (cs.NE) and the use of empirical risks (cs.AI), which further support these sub-categories.
